\begin{verbatim}
readuff(filename::String) -> Vector{UFFDataset}
\end{verbatim}
Reads a UFF (Universal File Format) file and parses its contents into a vector of UFFDataset objects.

\textbf{Input}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{filename::String}: The path to the UFF file to be read.

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{data::Vector\{UFFDataset\}}: A vector containing the parsed UFF datasets.

\end{itemize}
